us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FramePose3DReadOnly

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Pose3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFramePose3DBasics, FramePose3DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePose3D

    public interface FramePose3DReadOnly
extends Pose3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder
    Read-only interface for a 3D pose expressed in a given reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Pose3DReadOnly, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FramePose3DReadOnly. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on poses occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FramePose3DReadOnly extends Pose3DReadOnly, it is compatible with methods only requiring Pose3DReadOnly. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FramePose3DReadOnly.

      • getRotationVector

        default void getRotationVector(FixedFrameVector3DBasics rotationVectorToPack)
        Computes and packs the orientation described by the orientation part of this pose as a rotation vector.

        WARNING: a rotation vector is different from a yaw-pitch-roll or Euler angles representation. A rotation vector is equivalent to the axis of an axis-angle that is multiplied by the angle of the same axis-angle.

        Parameters:
        rotationVectorToPack - the vector in which the rotation vector is stored. Modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if rotationVectorToPack is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.

      • epsilonEquals

        default boolean epsilonEquals(FramePose3DReadOnly other,
                              double epsilon)
        Tests if this pose is equal to the given other to an epsilon.

        If the two poses have different frames, this method returns false.

        Parameters:
        other - the other pose to compare against this. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use when comparing..
        Returns:
        true if the two poses are equal and are expressed in the same reference frame, false otherwise.

      • geometricallyEquals

        default boolean geometricallyEquals(FramePose3DReadOnly other,
                                    double epsilon)
        Compares this to other to determine if the two poses are geometrically similar.

        Two poses are geometrically equal if both their position and orientation are geometrically equal.

        Parameters:
        other - the pose to compare to. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance of the comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the two poses represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.
